  "text": "Densities of P. centralis larvae in the Sand River were less than 10 larvae mp2 [CITATION_1] . The density tolerated by larvae in the spacing experiment was equivalent to 1600 larvae*mp'; it thus seems unlikely that spacing is an important determinant of field densities, even given that actively foraging individuals would probably tolerate only a much lower density.",
